\f0\b\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Dc link voltage (Excitation voltage) 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 The DC Link Voltage is internally measured from rectified voltage of excitation input power. This signal is used for protective function and monitoring purpose. The monitored excitation voltage of the HDCM software is not value directly measured from excitation output terminal but calculated from dc link voltage by using PWM duty and voltage drop of power module (IGBT). 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 Excitation current 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 This signal is internally measured from output current of power module (IGBT) by using of current sensor installed in HDEC2000 unit. This signal is used for the excitation current control, over excitation limitation, protective functions and monitoring purpose. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 Excitation power 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 Three kinds of Excitation input power source (Shunt power, PMG power and External utility) are available. Three phase ac. source, single phase ac. source, or dc power source is usable and the permissible maximum voltage is 260Vac or 360Vdc. The input power is rectified and smoothed by capacitor, and then supplied to excitation winding through the power module (IGBT). 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 The current ratings of excitation input power source and all other components carrying excitation current are not calculated from the power rating of HDEC2000 unit, but should be determined from design data of the generator. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 If the excitation input voltage is much higher than the excitation requirement, the dynamic response is improved but control accuracy or stability may be reduced.\uc0\u8232 On the other hand if the margin of excitation input voltage is a little bit higher than excitation requirement, the control accuracy or stability may be improved, but the dynamic response may be very poor. The balance between dynamic response and control accuracy is the first consideration in the designation of excitation system (input power). See Appendix C (Specification) for more information. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 Control power 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 HDEC2000 unit does not require the external control power for the most of application. In case of external control power is supplied depending on application, some consideration may be made. For more information, see Voltage Buildup function of this section, section 2 (Installation and Hardware) and Appendix C (Specification). 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Digital (Relay) Output 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 HDEC2000 unit provides three programmable output relays and one watchdog relay. The output relays are controlled by DSP (digital signal processor) and the power rating is 250Vac, 10A.\uc0\u8232 Even though the current rating of relays is 10A, we strongly recommend that the output relay be used with the control purpose only for the robustness of overall excitation system. 
\f1\fs24 \

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 If the output relay is connected with reactive load (ex: relay coil) in dc circuit, the load should have freewheeling diode across the load terminals, or the freewheeling diode should be installed externally to protect the circuit against switching arc. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

