\f0\b\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 Memory usage and configuration 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 Three types of memories (Flash memory, RAM and EEPROM) are internally used for HDEC2000 unit operation. EEPROM stores configuration parameters, and user can access (readable and writable) to this information via HDCM software. Executable control software code (firmware) is stored in the nonvolatile Flash memory integrated in the DSP. RAM is used for temporary data storage, and it is also integrated in the DSP. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 OPERATIONAL FUNCTION 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 This section describes control modes, limitation functions and protective functions of HDEC2000 unit. The helpful technical information is also described for understanding the internal architecture of the unit. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

